        <div class="verdict">✓ Updated April 2026</div>

        <p>Houzz Pro and Construction Online (from UDA Technologies) both target residential general contractors and custom home builders, but they've made different bets about what matters most. Houzz Pro has invested heavily in the client experience — a marketplace that generates leads, a polished client portal, and design-forward tools for selections and proposals. Construction Online has focused on project management depth — scheduling, document management, contracts, and field reporting.</p>

        <p>Your choice often depends on where your biggest pain points are: client communication and lead generation, or project scheduling and field documentation.</p>

