        <h2>Where Houzz Pro wins</h2>

        <h3>The Houzz marketplace — built-in lead generation</h3>
        <p>Houzz Pro's most significant differentiator isn't a software feature — it's access to the Houzz marketplace, where millions of homeowners actively search for contractors. A well-maintained Houzz Pro profile generates qualified leads from homeowners who are actively planning projects. For contractors who struggle with lead generation, this built-in demand channel can justify the subscription cost on its own.</p>
        <p>Construction Online has no equivalent lead generation capability — it's purely a project management tool. If marketing and lead flow are pain points, Houzz Pro addresses them directly.</p>

        <h3>Client selections and design tools</h3>
        <p>Houzz Pro's selections feature is the best client-facing selection tool in construction software. Contractors create curated option boards for finishes, fixtures, and materials; clients browse and select with budget impact shown in real time; approved selections automatically update the project budget. This workflow is genuinely elegant and clients — particularly in high-end residential remodeling — respond well to it.</p>
        <p>Construction Online's selection tools are functional but lack the visual polish and marketplace integration that makes Houzz Pro's selections feel modern and client-appropriate.</p>

        <h3>Proposals and client communication</h3>
        <p>Houzz Pro's proposal workflow is designed for the residential sales process: visually polished proposals with photos and descriptions, digital signature collection, and automated follow-up. The overall client communication experience — from first contact through project completion — is more polished than Construction Online's.</p>

        <h3>Price entry point</h3>
        <p>At $99/month, Houzz Pro is meaningfully more affordable than Construction Online's starting price around $299/month. For smaller contractors or those early in their technology adoption journey, Houzz Pro offers solid functionality at a lower commitment level.</p>

