        <h2>Where Construction Online wins</h2>

        <h3>Project scheduling depth</h3>
        <p>Construction Online's scheduling module is more powerful than Houzz Pro's for complex project scheduling. Full Gantt charts with task dependencies, critical path tracking, resource allocation, and schedule baseline comparisons give project managers the tools they need to manage multi-month custom home projects. Houzz Pro's Gantt is functional but lighter — fine for remodeling projects, limiting for complex custom builds.</p>

        <h3>Daily logs and field reporting</h3>
        <p>Construction Online's daily log module is comprehensive: crew headcount, weather, work performed, subcontractor activity, equipment, visitors, and delays — all in a structured daily report that creates a legal-grade project record. For custom home builders managing complex site operations, this documentation depth is important for warranty claims, dispute resolution, and project management visibility.</p>

        <h3>Document management</h3>
        <p>Construction Online's document management is stronger for companies with complex document needs: plan versioning, specification management, RFI tracking, submittal logs, and contract document organization. For custom home builders managing extensive contract documents, plan sets, and specifications, Construction Online's document center provides better organization.</p>

        <h3>Subcontractor coordination</h3>
        <p>Construction Online's subcontractor management module handles bid solicitation, sub agreements, and coordination better than Houzz Pro. For GCs managing large subcontractor networks, the ability to send RFPs, collect bids, and manage sub contracts within the platform adds value that Houzz Pro doesn't provide.</p>

        <h2>Who should choose Houzz Pro?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Remodelers and design-build contractors who want built-in lead generation</li>
          <li>Contractors competing for high-end residential clients where presentation matters</li>
          <li>Businesses where the selection process is a significant part of the client experience</li>
          <li>Smaller contractors who need an accessible price point</li>
          <li>Contractors whose biggest pain point is marketing and lead flow</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Who should choose Construction Online?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom home builders managing complex multi-month projects</li>
          <li>GCs who need deep scheduling tools with dependencies and critical path</li>
          <li>Companies with complex document management and subcontractor coordination needs</li>
          <li>Contractors who already have good lead flow and primarily need project execution tools</li>
        </ul>

